info.description:
=====
Django-Csv
=====

Django-Csv-Tabulation is a simple app which is take the data from the uploaded csv file and do the cross tabulation

Detailed documentation is in the "docs" directory.

Quick start
-----------

1. Add "django-csv" to your INSTALLED_APPS setting like this::

    INSTALLED_APPS = (
        ...
        'django-csv',
    )

2. Include the django-csv URLconf in your project urls.py like this::

    url(r'^', include('django-csv.urls')),

3. Run `python manage.py migrate` to create the django-csv models.

4. Start the development server and visit http://127.0.0.1:8000/admin/
   to create a csv data (you'll need the Admin app enabled).

5. Visit http://127.0.0.1:8000/ to participate in the django-csv.
